
                                            Ramaphosa says that leaders must commit themselves to achieving the complete liberation of all citizens.

                                         JOHANNESBURG - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa says the country needs more revolutionary leaders as the ANC prepares for its elective conference in December. Addressing a Cadres Forum in Mahikeng, in the North West, Ramaphosa says the country needs leaders who will be able to address the needs of poor South Africans. He says the leaders must commit themselves to achieving the complete liberation of all citizens. “Our country needs more cadres who have a revolutionary character and an unwavering commitment to the cause to the poor people of the country.” 